<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,493,1138]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis box="[151,218,493,518]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Bulbs</emphasis>
subglobose, 
<emphasis box="[372,423,493,518]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">app.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[430,488,493,519]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
in diameter, tunics greyish-brown. 
<emphasis box="[905,986,493,518]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Leaves</emphasis>
1 or 2, elliptic to oblong, thick fleshy, basally enclosing the scape, the upper side sulcate, glaucous and basally reddish-brown, margin red and scabrous, 
<quantity box="[270,373,570,596]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="cm" value="13.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="7.0">7–20 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[450,561,570,596]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="cm" value="2.25" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–3 cm</quantity>
wide. 
<emphasis box="[643,714,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Scape</emphasis>
cylindrical, straight, shorter than leaves, 
<quantity box="[1209,1298,570,596]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="cm" value="5.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="2.0">2–8 cm</quantity>
above soil, 
<emphasis box="[151,202,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">app.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[210,279,609,635]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in diameter, glaucous green. 
<taxonomicName box="[628,708,609,634]" genus="Spathe" kingdom="Plantae" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[628,708,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Spathe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
membranous, splitting into 2–4 shortly acuminate parts, with brownish nerves. 
<emphasis box="[374,455,648,673]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Umbel</emphasis>
semi-globose to subglobose, contracted, many-flowered, 
<quantity box="[1186,1278,648,674]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 cm</quantity>
in diameter. 
<emphasis box="[151,253,687,712]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Pedicels</emphasis>
straight, up to 
<quantity box="[438,522,686,712]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
long, purplish. 
<emphasis box="[715,813,687,712]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Flowers</emphasis>
flat star-like. 
<emphasis box="[985,1062,687,712]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Tepals</emphasis>
long-triangular, longitudinally folded, acute, 
<quantity box="[317,414,725,751]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
long, basally 
<quantity box="[580,699,725,751]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1 mm</quantity>
wide, white, with brownish mid-vein, after anthesis convolute but not prickly stiff. 
<emphasis box="[405,525,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Filaments</emphasis>
4/5 to nearly as long as tepals, violet, with whitish base, subulate, basally connate and united with tepals. 
<emphasis box="[531,683,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Anthers app.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[692,783,802,828]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long, violet. 
<emphasis box="[943,1017,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Ovary</emphasis>
depressed globose with three deep furrows, coarse, 
<emphasis box="[351,403,841,866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">app.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[411,480,841,867]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in diameter, violet, after anthesis greenish. 
<emphasis box="[1006,1063,841,866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Style</emphasis>
conical, 
<quantity box="[1173,1272,841,867]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
long, whitish violet, stigma undivided. 
<emphasis box="[451,547,880,905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Capsule</emphasis>
depressed tripartite with furrows, 
<quantity box="[953,1050,880,906]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1125,1223,880,906]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
diameter, in fresh state greenish, in dry state brownish. 
<emphasis box="[590,657,919,944]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Seeds</emphasis>
one per locule, depressed ovate, 
<quantity box="[1049,1168,918,944]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2–2.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1244,1364,918,944]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1–1.5 mm</quantity>
wide, 
<emphasis box="[151,202,957,982]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">app.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[209,276,957,983]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
thick, shiny black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,493,1138]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,995,1021]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet refers to Aladagh mountain range in SW of the capital city of Bojnord in North 
<collectingRegion box="[257,495,1034,1060]" country="Iran" name="Khorasan-e Shomali" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Khorassan province</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,493,1138]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,338,1072,1098]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Phenology:</emphasis>
—An ephemeroid species, leaf sprouting is initiated in May, flowering and fruiting is completed in mid-June (
<figureCitation box="[435,504,1112,1138]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1943,1964]" captionTargetBox="[377,1219,1201,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-367@1.[376,1223,1201,1922]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Allium aladaghense in its natural habitat. A–B: the type location at Mt. Aladagh, A. Habit; B. A small population on stony slopes with grazed leaves. C–D: the localities at Mt. Salook, C. Plants growing in the thorn cushion Acantholimon erinaceum, a nurse bush for A. aladaghense; D. The plants in fruiting stage." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5061126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5061126/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5061126" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5061126" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5061126/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" startId="1.[151,244,1943,1964]" targetBox="[377,1219,1201,1921]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1943,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,261,1943,1964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">FIGURE 1</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Memariani &amp; Joharchi" authorityYear="2012" box="[272,463,1943,1964]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aladaghense">
<emphasis box="[272,463,1943,1964]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Allium aladaghense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its natural habitat. A–B: the type location at Mt. Aladagh, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1045,1069,1943,1964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">A.</emphasis>
Habit; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1139,1161,1943,1964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">B.</emphasis>
A small population on stony slopes with grazed leaves. C–D: the localities at Mt. Salook, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[736,759,1976,1997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">C.</emphasis>
Plants growing in the thorn cushion 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linczevski" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Jaubert &amp; Spach" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[1113,1355,1977,1998]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plumbaginaceae" genus="Acantholimon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erinaceum">
<emphasis box="[1113,1355,1977,1998]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">Acantholimon erinaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a nurse bush for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Memariani &amp; Joharchi" authorityYear="2012" box="[236,384,2010,2031]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aladaghense">
<emphasis box="[236,384,2010,2031]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">A. aladaghense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[396,420,2009,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="29">D.</emphasis>
The plants in fruiting stage.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,448]" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,512,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—So far, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Memariani &amp; Joharchi" authorityYear="2012" box="[627,807,152,177]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aladaghense">
<emphasis box="[627,807,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">A. aladaghense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in higher elevations of Aladagh range and Salook summit in NE 
<collectingCountry box="[414,461,190,216]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[477,550,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1014,1035]" captionTargetBox="[332,1254,502,995]" captionTargetId="figure-481@2.[332,1254,502,995]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution map of Allium sect. Asteroprason subsect. Asteroprason including the new species, A. aladaghense (white circle) and its closely related species, A. kuhsorkhense (black circle), according to the vouchers seen by the authors." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5061130" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5061130/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). It grows on north and northwest facing stony slopes, between 
<quantity metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.475" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.35" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" unit="m" value="2475.0" valueMax="2600.0" valueMin="2350.0">2350–2600 m</quantity>
<emphasis box="[183,242,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">a.s.l.</emphasis>
